OL,6,F"The ad showed a black teenage boy
OL,7,Fverbally harassing a white girl. While
OL,8,Fthe white male friend was shown in the
OL,9,Fad and the two-minute film, the ad did
OL,10,Fnot show him as jointly intimidating
OL,11,Fthe victim. The only aggressor in the
OL,12,Fad was the black teenage boy.
OL,14,F"Although we understood that TfL had
OL,15,Fintended to present a range of
OL,16,Fdiversity and scenarios across their
OL,17,Fcampaign, we considered the ad, when
OL,18,Fseen in isolation, had the effect of
OL,19,Fperpetuating a negative racial
OL,20,Fstereotype about black men as
OL,21,Fperpetrators of threatening behaviour.
