OL,6,F"On that basis, we concluded that the
OL,7,Fad featured a harmful stereotype, was
OL,8,Firresponsible and likely to cause
OL,9,Fserious offence."
OL,11,FThe ASA ruled that the ad must not
OL,12,Fappear again in the form complained
OL,13,Fabout, adding: "We told TfL to ensure
OL,14,Fthat future ads were socially
OL,15,Fresponsible. We also told them to
OL,16,Favoid perpetuating harmful stereotypes
OL,17,Fand causing serious offence on the
OL,18,Fgrounds of race."
